id: pm-nb08
title: "Daily auto-release silently blocked 06-14..16 by a single stale unresolved Sentry error (sentry-telemetry-gate is:unresolved has no time window)"
description: "auto-release.yml (cron 02:35) failed 2026-06-14/15/16 (last success 06-13) because sentry-telemetry-gate reported high=1 against max_high=0. The gate queries 'is:unresolved level:[fatal,error]' with NO time bound, so any single lingering unresolved error/fatal issue (even an old benign one nobody resolved in Sentry) blocks EVERY daily release until manually resolved, with no alerting — 3 releases were silently skipped. On 06-17 the offending issue had aged out (high=0) and I manually dispatched the catch-up release (v2026.6.16 published). Proposed durable fix (needs maintainer call as it loosens a safety gate): bound the gate query to a recent window (e.g. age:-14d or firstSeen/lastSeen window) and/or add failure alerting so a blocked daily release notifies instead of silently skipping. Related: pm-ehbb (nightly failure alerting)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-16T22:33:08.059Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-19T05:58:34.208Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-5oj5
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-19T05:58:34.208Z",claude-code-agent,"Release-health verification 2026-06-19: the recent scheduled auto-release FAILURES (06-17T07:36, 06-18T07:17) were NOT this Sentry-gate path — they were the git push non-fast-forward race (bare 'git push origin HEAD' losing to concurrent main pushes), tracked+fixed by pm-5oti (commit bf35af26, merged 06-18 16:19 with --atomic + fetch/rebase/retry). Both failures predate that fix, so 06-19 will be the first scheduled run WITH it. Sentry reliability gate currently PASSES: critical=0, high=0 (this issue's stale-error class no longer blocks). Telemetry stack healthy: all containers up, RabbitMQ backlog 0, 14785 events/24h, full error-code coverage. No release published since v2026.6.17 (21+ commits pending incl PR#297)."
